AB  - In the version of “Are Stocks Real Assets? Sticky Discount Rates in Stock Markets” by Michael Katz, Hanno Lustig and Lars Nielsen (10.1093/rfs/hhw072) that originally published online, the introduction mistakenly stated:“it is natural that stock investors with a limited capacity to process information would update firm-level nominal cash flow forecasts more frequently than economy-wide inflation forecasts in cash flows.”
